column1: #Text=Lansdowne , commonly confused with Lansdale , Pennsylvania , is a small , quaint town located thirty minutes outside the city of Philadelphia .
#Text=Lansdowne is 1.2 square miles in size with a population of a little over 11,000 .
#Text=Lansdowne is very community-based , with many community groups , such as boys and girls clubs , boys scout and girl scout troops , American Legion Posts , and many more .
#Text=Lansdowne also has many places of worship and private and parochial schools .
#Text=Lansdowne might be small on area and population , but it is bulging at the seams with history .
#Text=The 101 Media , and 102 Sharon Hill trolleys both run through Lansdowne along with the Media/Elwyn Line train , 109 , 113 , and Route 30 buses as well as various other forms of SEPTA .
#Text=It is easy to figure out how to ride SEPTA through their website :
#Text=You can also drive into town and park your car in one of the many parking lots and begin your walking tour throughout one of many historic districts .
#Text=You can fly into Philadelphia International Airport and rent a car or take a taxi , if you do not live within driving distance .
#Text=Lansdowne provides walking tours throughout its historic districts .
#Text=Hosts several wonderful live plays by the Celebration Theater .
#Text=Tickets for these wonderful performances are only $ 17 for adults , $ 15 for students and seniors , and $ 12 for children .
#Text=Other than exploring the beautiful history of Lansdowne , there are plenty of activities to participate in .
#Text=Is a 75-piece orchestra which has been performing for over 50 years .
#Text=Tickets $ 15 for adults , $ 12 for seniors , and $ 5 for students .
#Text=Lansdowne Folk Club has folk music concerts .
#Text=There are also nine lovely borough parks :
#Text=8 acres with baseball and soccer fields , basketball courts , four tennis courts , pavilion , swings bathrooms and picnic tables .
#Text=1.2 acres with basketball courts , tot-lot toys , swings , slide and picnic tables .
#Text=3 acres with basketball courts , tot-lot toys , swings and slide .
#Text=Belmont Park , Belmont and Plumstead Aves . 3.9 acres with basketball courts , swings , slide , tot-lot toys and big toys .
#Text=Home of the symbol of Lansdowne , its 300 year old Sycamore tree .
#Text=6.5 acres of County open space with Lansdowne Bird Sanctuary .
#Text=Shrigley Woods , Scottdale and Hilldale Rds . 6.5 acres of undeveloped County open space .
#Text=Marlyn Park , Willowbrook and Marlyn Aves . 3 acres , passive park .
#Text=Lansdowne Avenue has many small shops including nail salons , clothing shops , flower shops , dollar stores , convenience stores , gift shops , and other small businesses .
#Text=Most of the restaurants are small , family-owned and very inexpensive .
#Text=Great Wall Chinese Restaurant , 7 N Lansdowne Ave.
#Text=B 's Que Shot Lounge , 527 E Baltimore Ave.
#Text=Lansdowne is a dry town , but the city of Philadelphia , which is only thirty minutes away , has a great night life .
#Text=There are also several beer distributors and liquor stores bordering Lansdowne on all sides .
#Text=There are no hotels located directly in Lansdowne , but there are several very close by in Upper Darby and Philadelphia .
